-- Portugal Wants Extra 10% Cut in Government Spending, Jornal Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-03-27T07:24:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/portugal-wants-extra-10-cut-in-government-spending-jornal-says.html
Portugal  wants to cut spending by
an additional 10 percent in all government services in the 2013
to 2015 period,  Jornal de Negocios said , citing an internal
document from the  Finance Ministry .  A substantial part of the effort to reduce expenditures by
at least 10 percent should start to take place next year, the
Portuguese newspaper said, citing the document.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
 halmeida5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
